* property generally is a good thing, but intellectual property is bad; it defends the interest of the property holder, but hurts the property of the general people, more precisely : their freedom [freedom is a property [the most important one]] to act even without unfairly using other people's work; because the intellectual property puts a big administrative, risk and constraint burdon on the people
